 also makes that kind of bug very hard to find: by the time you get<br />the kernel Oops the thing that corrupted the list is long gone already. <br /><br />I'll see if I can make it a bit more resistant to programming errors in<br />the kernel (by moving the free page lists into the "mem_map[]" array, so<br />that the list isn't in the free page itself).  That won't make whatever<br />bug go away, but it might make it easier to debug (when the crash<br />hopefully happens in a less critical section). <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
